# Test: two-tier overflow pool delivers all routes under burst
# VALIDATES: AC-10/AC-11 -- overflow items use MixedBufMux handles
# VALIDATES: AC-12 -- pool exhaustion does not drop routes
# STATUS: Phase 5 (spec-ci-observer-per-test-audit) -- runtime_fail wired;
#         AC verification is TODO. Same architectural blocker as
#         community-strip: this test loads only bgp-adj-rib-in and does
#         NOT load any plugin that calls ForwardUpdate (e.g. bgp-rs or
#         bgp-cache), so the forward pool is never exercised and adj-rib-in
#         receives routes via a path affected by the rpki validation gate.
#         Negative regression assertions catch obvious breaks until the
#         redesign chooses Path A (load a forwarding plugin) or Path B
#         (switch dest peer to ze-peer check mode).
# PREVENTS: routes silently dropped during overflow, pool handle leaks
#
# Flow:
# 1. Source peer sends 50 UPDATEs (burst exceeds per-peer pool of 64 slots)
# 2. Routes would forward through ze to dest peer in the designed behaviour
# 3. Python observer queries metrics for ze_bgp_pool_used_ratio (smoke check)
# 4. AC-10/AC-11/AC-12 cannot be verified without a forwarding plugin

# Source peer (ASN 65001) -- sends 100 prefixes in a burst
option=env:var=ze.log.bgp.reactor.session:value=debug
stdin=source:terminator=EOF_SOURCE
option=tcp_connections:value=1
option=timeout:value=20s

# Send 100 UPDATEs: 10.0.0.0/24 through 10.0.99.0/24
# Each UPDATE: ORIGIN=IGP, AS_PATH=[65001], NEXT_HOP=1.1.1.1, LOCAL_PREF=100
# Base hex: header(19B marker + 2B len + 1B type=2) + body
# Withdrawn=0x0000, attrs=0x15 bytes, NLRI=0x180A00XX00
# We send them as individual UPDATEs to maximize per-item dispatch pressure.
action=send:conn=1:seq=1:hex=FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF00300200000015400101004002004003040101010140050400000064180A000000
